 {
  "text": "First, wanting to make a good impression, she struck up a conversation at the reception. She asked where the tour met, which sounded tactful and polite. During an awkward lull, she read the room and gently changed the subject. They quickly hit it off and built a warm rapport. Finally, her indirect questions had put everyone at ease, and the evening flew by.",
